e (see Tips)","40 g fresh ginger, peeled and cut into thin slices","2 tbsp soy sauce","2 tsp sesame oil","4 skinless chicken breast fillets (approx. 700 g), cut lengthways into quarters","3 spring onions\/shallots, cut into thin slices, to serve","20 fresh mint leaves (approx. 2 sprigs), to serve","100 g cucumber, cut into thin slices, to serve"]}],"id":"r138000","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-dz-A_sRdcBg\/XZQwOqpkh-I\/AAAAAAAAckE\/eznYwxXOPw8rUW4kNVrYDp_8ru-449HcQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_ViQ9VZS6OVVcN2wI.png","title":"Com ga rau thom (chicken with rice and mint)","publishedAt":"2017-05-14T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"47.5 g","fat":"7 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"67.3 g","calories":"2259 kJ \/ 538 kcal"},"usefulItems":"bowl, thermal serving bowl or other large bowl, serving bowls","hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to <em>The Basic Cookbook <\/em>or <em>Everyday Cookbook <\/em>for the Chicken stock paste recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h","4 portions"]}